&lt;pre&gt;To close the loop - thanks to the feedback (i.e. pointing out that the CL
causes a broad slowdown) I was able to identify the root problem: some
low-level, performance-sensitive pieces of Rust standard library were
getting instrumented for code coverage - see &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://crbug.com/395690207"&gt;https://crbug.com/395690207&lt;/a&gt;
for more details.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Thank you for your help!

On Mon, Feb 10, 2025 at 1:11 PM Weizhong Xia &lt;weizh...@google.com&gt; wrote:

