&lt;h1&gt;
&lt;span class="subject"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=subject:%22%5C%5Bblink%5C-dev%5C%5D+%5C%5BFYI%5C%5D+All+predefined+color+spaces+can+now+be+used+for+gradients%22&amp;o=newest" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="name"&gt;[blink-dev] [FYI] All predefined color spaces can now be used for gradients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class="darkgray font13"&gt;
&lt;span class="sender pipe"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=from:%22Aaron+Krajeski%22" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="name"&gt;Aaron Krajeski&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="date"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=date:20250212" rel="nofollow"&gt;Wed, 12 Feb 2025 10:57:14 -0800&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div itemprop="articleBody" class="msgBody"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;Display P3, Rec2020, ProPhoto RGB and a98 RGB are specified in CSS color 4 
as predefined color spaces but had not yet been implemented as color spaces 
for interpolation:
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/#predefined"&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/#predefined&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Recently the functionality was added to Skia 
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/942876"&gt;https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/942876&lt;/a&gt;&gt; and the interface 
added to Blink 
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/6202302"&gt;https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/6202302&lt;/a&gt;&gt; so as 
of M134 these four color spaces will be useable in gradients!

A demo: &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://codepen.io/mysterydate/pen/azbzvqB"&gt;https://codepen.io/mysterydate/pen/azbzvqB&lt;/a&gt;

Please contact me with any concerns or questions, if not, enjoy gradients!
  Aaron

